comments: Nurkic (POR) briefly places an arm around Jokic (DEN) and then removes it as the two players engage and disengage.
Dozier (DEN) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Nurkic (POR) and firms up on his left leg.
There is no clear and conclusive video evidence that Jokic (DEN) steps out of bounds.
Replay review of the foul on Nurkic (POR) pursuant to a coach's challenge is deemed unsuccessful.  Nurkic makes contact to Jokic's (DEN) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Covington (POR) has an arm in Dozier's (DEN) path when he sets the screen but the contact is marginal.
Gordon (DEN) and Nurkic (POR) make incidental contact with each other as they go up for the rebound.
Jokic (DEN) maintains his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Nurkic (POR) makes contact to Jokic's (DEN) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Dozier (DEN) jumps to contest the driving shot attempt by Lillard (POR) and marginal contact occurs that does not affect the shot attempt.
Nurkic (POR) briefly places an arm on Jokic's (DEN) back and does not affect his FOM.  Jokic raises his arms, drawing attention to the marginal contact.
Nurkic (POR) legally contests Jokic's (DEN) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.

Lillard (POR) and Covington (POR) both get their hands on the ball after Gordon (DEN) grabs the rebound and any contact is incidental.  A held ball is correctly whistled between Gordon and Lillard, who gets his hand on the ball before Covington.
Powell (POR) makes incidental contact with Dozier (DEN) while the ball is loose.
Jokic (DEN) legally contests Powell's (POR) driving shot attempt.
